Egyptian Stocks: Egyptian Resorts, Palm Hills, Orascom

-- B y   A h m e d   A   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-06-09T14:27:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/egyptian-stocks-egyptian-resorts-maridive-oil-services.html
Egypt ’s benchmark EGX 30 Index
advanced 1.3 percent to 5,504.6 at the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo,
the highest level since June 1. The gauge has gained 2.6 percent
this week.  The following shares rose or fell in Cairo. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Egyptian Resorts Co. (EGTS)   climbed 2 percent, the most
since May 29, to 1 Egyptian pound. The Red Sea resorts developer
reported a first-quarter profit of 3.75 million Egyptian pounds
after a loss of 1.86 million pounds a year earlier.  Palm Hills Developments SAE (PHDC)   rose for the first
time in four days, gaining 2.3 percent to 2.24 pounds. The
Cairo-based real-estate developer appointed Mohamed Sultan as
chief executive officer, replacing Yassin Mansour. The company
plans to deliver 1,210 units in six months.  Orascom Construction Industries (OCIC)   jumped 4.1
percent, the most since March 29, to 283.3 pounds. Egypt’s
biggest publicly traded builder said it will buy back 440,000
shares from June 14 to July 13.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  